Street Closures Due to Reconstruction of Pavements January - March 2025

Between January and March of this year, the Department of Transportation (DOT) has closed off various

streets throughout NYC to redo pavements. Of all five boroughs, Queens had the most top layer removal

(milling) and resurfacing of pavements (paving) of roads throughout the city.
